A human leg has been found at a recycling plant in Dublin, local police has confirmed.

The alarm was raised late last night after the body part was discovered at the Thornton's plant in Ballyfermot, west Dublin.

Garda was called to the scene where a doctor confirmed that the limb was human, and part of the recycling centre has been closed down for forensic examinations to take place.

