Thornton's have yet to comment on the incident, but it is offering counselling to its staff at the plant in Ballyfermot, Irish Independent said.

Thornton's Recycling is the main waste management company on Ireland.

It recovers 85 per cent of the country's waste and operates a number of recycling and recovery facilities in Dublin, Meath and Kildare.

The company employs more than 300 members of staff and operates a fleet of over 100 waste recycling trucks.

